Šternfeld won in 1934 the Prix REP-Hirsch founded by Robert Esnault-Pelterie and André Louis Hirsch for "Introduction to Cosmonautics".
Dr. Jan Gadomski (1899 - 1966) later became an important defender of astronomy and space.
In Polish magazines, he published hundreds of articles and wrote several books on these scientific disciplines.
Gadomski's worldwide recognised contribution to the development of space, among other things, was appreciated by the name of one of the craters on the earthly side of the moon after him.
